The paper deals with a problem related to data management and movement in a distributed system, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the problem involves coordination and communication between multiple devices, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm to solve the problem, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
